  "abstract": "Corrects the wrong defaults a capable model has when designing a relational schema, covering the decisions where it imports ORM habits that discard referential integrity — polymorphic foreign keys, reflexive surrogate keys, one-to-one splits, blanket soft-delete flags — and the ones where it leaves an invariant to application code that the engine could prove instead. Examples are PostgreSQL 18, executed against 18.4 including their failure cases.",
